'''''Melica lilloi''''' is a species of [[grass]] in the [[Poaceae]] family that can be found in [[Catamarca Province|Catamarca]] and [[Tucum<U+00E1>n Province|Tucum<U+00E1>n]] provinces of [[Argentina]] on the elevation of {{convert|3200|-|3500|m}}.<ref name=Torres>{{cite journal|author=Torres, A.M.|year=1980|title=Revision de las especies Argentinas del genero Melica L. (Gramineae)|publisher=Opera Lilloana|volume=29|pages=1<U+2013>113}}</ref>

==Description==
The species is [[perennial plant|perennial]] with short [[rhizome]]s. The [[culm (plant)|culms]] are decumbent and are {{convert|30|<U+2013>|50|cm}} long with smooth [[plant stem|interlode]]s. The leaf-sheaths are scabrous, tubular, are closed on one end. The leaf-blades are flat, {{convert|8|<U+2013>|15|mm}} long by {{convert|1.5|mm}} wide and have an acute apex and ciliated margin. Both the leaf-sheaths and leaf-blades have a [[glabrousness|glabrous]] surface. The membrane is eciliated and is {{convert|1|-|1.5|mm}} long. The [[panicle]] is open, linear and is {{convert|10|<U+2013>|15|cm}} long.<ref name=kew>{{cite web|url=http://www.kew.org/data/grasses-db/www/imp06156.htm|author=W.D. Clayton, M. Vorontsova, K.T. Harman & H. Williamson|title=''Melica lilloi''|publisher=GrassBase|work=The Board of Trustees, [[Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew|Royal Botanic Gardens]]|location=[[Kew]]}}</ref>

Spikelets are elliptic, solitary, are {{convert|6.5|-|8|mm}} long and have fertile spikelets that are [[pedicel (botany)|pediceled]]. The pedicels are filiform, curved, pubescent, and hairy above. The spikelets have 1-2 fertile [[floret]]s which is diminished at the apex while the sterile florets are barren, cuneate, and [[Sessility (zoology)|clumped]] with its floret [[callus]] being glabrous. Both the upper and lower [[chaff|glumes]] are keellessm, membranous and have acute apexes. Their other features are different; Lower glume is obovate, {{convert|6.3|-|7.7|mm}} long and have an erosed apex while the upper one is lanceolate, {{convert|6|<U+2013>|7.5|mm}} long and have obtuse apex. The species' [[lemma (botany)|lemma]] have scaberulous surface and have emarginate apex as well. Its fertile lemma is chartaceous and lanceolated  that is {{convert|6|<U+2013>|7|mm}} long and {{convert|2|<U+2013>|2.3|mm}} wide. Its [[palea (botany)|palea]] have ciliolated keels, is {{convert|4|<U+2013>|5|mm}} long and have puberulous surface with hairy back. Flowers are fleshy, oblong, truncate and are {{convert|0.2|<U+2013>|0.3|mm}} long. They also grow together, and have 3 [[stamen|anther]]s that are {{convert|1.5|-|1.7|mm}} long. The [[fruit]]s are [[caryopsis]] with additional pericarp and linear [[hilum (biology)|hilum]].<ref name=kew/>

==Ecology==
Its [[flower]]ing time is from December to January.<ref name=Torres/>

